name: Faceted Gray Agate Briolette Pendant
description:
Like fog on a summer day slowly sweeping through the hills...
This slightly-faceted gray briolette pendant has intricate swirls of gray, white, and reddish-brown.  The stone itself is approximately half an inch long.

Argentium sterling silver wire and a sterling silver jump ring were used in this creation.

name: Slice of Sun Raw Citrine Point Pendant
description: This organic, raw citrine point pendant has a pale, golden yellow point and a few blemishes on the stone, which adds to its uniqueness!  Argentium sterling silver wire and a sterling silver jump ring were used in this creation.

name: Pale Wooden Agate Duo Dangle
description:
Two pearly-hued, translucent wooden agate pebble stones comprise this simple dangle, with a crimp bead cover at the bottom for an originally unique look.  The stones have a few neat orange-brown striations on them.

A sterling silver jump ring and a sterling silver headpin were used in this creation.

name: Rainbow Moonstone Nugget Pendant
description:
This is a lovely, faceted, rectangular-shaped rainbow moonstone pendant with little blue flash, but has beautifully pale shades of red, orange, and pink.  The iridescent white shimmer of this pendant is not to be beat.  Please note that there are some organic green marks on this pendant, which add to its charm.  

A sterling silver jump ring and argentium sterling silver wire was used in this creation.  The stone is a little over half an inch in length.
